Terminal
A terminal is a text-based interface to interact with the operating system.
It allows users to input commands and view output.

Shell
he shell is the program that processes commands. Bash (Bourne Again Shell) is the most common.
It interprets user input and communicates with the kernel.

Man Pages (Manual Pages) 
Use the `man` command to view documentation for any Linux command.
 Structure includes: NAME, SYNOPSIS, DESCRIPTION, OPTIONS, EXAMPLES.
 Example: `man ls` shows all options for `ls`.
